				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If both the position and the speed have sub-pixel bits, there should be no problem. The speed should be affected by input (e.g. add X to it if right is pressed, as long as it's below the maximum) and level geometry (slopes, gravity, etc.), and added to the position every frame. If the position doesn't have sub-pixels, the fractional part of the speed will be ignored and will never build up to an entire pixel.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

